Here is a concise LATEX code to draw a chessboard from a FEN notation:

```latex
\usepackage{chessfss}

\newchessgame[id=mygame, fen=<FEN notation>]

\chessboard[id=mygame, pgfstyle=smallboard]
```

The `\usepackage{chessfss}` loads the chessfss package which provides the commands to draw chessboards. The `\newchessgame` defines a new chess game with the given FEN notation. The `\chessboard` then draws the board according to the game 'mygame' defined above.

Alternatively, you can use the "\chessboard" command from the "skak" package in LaTeX to draw a chessboard and display the FEN notation. Here's a sample code:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{skak}

\begin{document}

\fenboard{FEN_NOTATION}
\begin{center}
\chessboard
\end{center}

\end{document}
```

Replace "FEN_NOTATION" with the actual FEN notation of the chessboard you want to display. Remember to load the "skak" package in the preamble of your LaTeX document.

Another option is to use the chessboard, xskak, and chessfss packages. Here is a sample code:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{chessboard}
\usepackage{xskak}
